# Onboarding Report Standards

## All 9 sections required
Every report must include: Overview, Tech Stack, Directory Map, Key Commands, Test Setup, Risky Areas, Entry Points, First Good Tasks, Open Questions. Use "None identified" for empty sections — never omit them.

## First Good Tasks need complexity estimates
```markdown
<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
### First Good Tasks
1. **Add pagination to /v1/products endpoint** (Easy, ~1-2 hours)
   - File: app/api/v1/products.py
   - Existing test: tests/test_products.py

<!-- ❌ BAD — no location, no estimate -->
### First Good Tasks
1. Add pagination
```

## Static analysis only — no hallucination
If you can't determine something from the filesystem, write "Unable to determine from static analysis" rather than guessing.

## Reports are immutable after delivery
Never edit a report that has been delivered. Create a new one with an updated timestamp.
